  <prompt>
    Phase 4 exit gate. Produce a written verification report confirming all 25+ WP5 FRs (FR-25 through FR-37 + NFR-A1 through NFR-A7) are satisfied and architecture §8 tool surface (12 tools total: 8 new memory tools + 4 existing Pillar 6b workspace tools) is verified live in the deployed environment. Gate transitions the project from Phase 4 → Phase 5 (WP2 file-aware classification).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform program lead. Verification-only role; no implementation.</role>

  <goal>
    Phase 4 exit-gate report at `notes/handoffs/105-phase4-exit-gate.md` confirms: (a) all WP5 FRs satisfied per spec.md, (b) architecture §8 tool surface live, (c) NFR-A1–A7 architectural principles upheld, (d) FR-45 invariant at `PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs:627` preserved, (e) binding-NEGATIVE rules respected (no `spaarke-insights-index`/`MultiIndexComposer`/etc reads), (f) BFF publish-size cumulative within NFR-01. Pass-or-fail outcome triggers Phase 5 dispatch or human escalation.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 4 was the largest phase (42 tasks across 21 waves). The exit gate is the architectural-binding checkpoint before Phase 5 (WP2 file-aware classification — depends on FR-17 upload-manifest enrichment from Phase 4b). Per CLAUDE.md, exit gates are MINIMAL rigor — verification only — but the verification surface is broad. Reference architecture §8 for the canonical tool surface; spec.md FR-26 through FR-37 for WP5 functional acceptance; spec.md NFR-A1 through NFR-A7 for the architectural principles.
    </background>
